@startuml parallel-mergesort-game-flow
!theme plain
!include ../shared/theme.puml

' --- FONT SIZES ---
skinparam defaultFontSize 34
skinparam TitleFontSize 38
skinparam SwimlaneTitleFontSize 34
skinparam NoteFontSize 34
skinparam ActivityFontSize 34
skinparam ActivityDiamondFontSize 34
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam ArrowThickness 4 
 

' --- COLORS ---
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #F0F8FF
skinparam PartitionBackgroundColor #FAFAFA

title Performing Parallel Merge Sort with the Existing Tool

|#LightBlue|System|
|#LightGreen|All\nPlayers|
|#LightYellow|Merger\n(Main Thread)|
|#LightPink|Non-Merger\n(Blocked)|

|System|
start
:Generate **n** shuffled cards\nin shared container;
:Divide cards into **p** equal\npartitions (one per player);

note right
  Players decide
  before starting
  how to partition
  the cards.
end note
:Assign each partition\nto a player;

' FIX 1: We declare the partition BEFORE switching swimlanes. 
' FIX 2: Added \n at the end of the string to create vertical padding!
partition "**Phase 1 — Local Sort** (parallel, independent)\n" {
    
    |All\nPlayers|
    fork
        :Player 1 sorts\npartition 1\nusing local buffer;
    fork again
        :Player **p** sorts\npartition **p**\nusing local buffer;
    end fork
    
    :Each player clicks\n"Reach Barrier Done";
    
    note right
      Each player works **only**
      on their assigned zone.
      Buffer contiguity check
      enforces coherent subsets.
      ——
      **Maps to:**
      embarrassingly
      parallel local
      computation
    end note
}

|System|
:All local sorts validated;\n→ **Barrier activates**;
note right
  Reuses existing
  **BarrierManager** FSM:
  RUNNING → WAITING
  → BARRIER_ACTIVE
end note

' FIX 2: Added \n at the end of the string to push the repeat diamond down!
partition "**Phase 2 — Merge Rounds**\n(⌈log₂ p⌉ rounds)\n" {
    repeat
        :Pair adjacent players\nfor this merge round;
        note right
          Round **k**: merge
          2^(k-1)-size sorted
          runs into 2^k-size
        end note

        fork
            |Merger\n(Main Thread)|
            :Merge two adjacent\nsorted runs into one;
            note left
              Merger interacts
              with shared
              container. Other
              cards visible.
              ——
              **Maps to:**
              reduction /
              tree merging
            end note
        fork again
            |Non-Merger\n(Blocked)|
            :See lock overlay\n(barrier active);
            note left
              **Maps to:**
              thread idle time
              / sync cost
            end note
        end fork

        |System|
        :Validate merged run\nis sorted;
        :Release barrier\n→ next round;
    repeat while (More merge rounds?) is (yes)
    -> no;
}

|System|
:All cards in ascending order\n→ **Game complete!**;
note right
  Single fully sorted
  array in shared
  container. Show
  completion stats:
  time, moves, rounds.
end note
stop

center footer Players perform Parallel Merge Sort using existing shared container, buffers, and barriers

@enduml